Former Finance Minister, Dr. Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala has been appointed a member of the South Africa Presidential Economic Advisory Council. The Council met in Pretoria on Friday with President Cyril Ramaphosa presiding. The meeting, according to her, discussed “sources of growth for the South African economy and win-win economic interactions with the continent.” Okonjo-Iweala shared some of the photographs taken at the meeting on her Twitter handle.